05gene_annotation

This workflow prepares RNA and protein evidence for BRAKER3, then runs annotation.

Main steps:
- stage soft-masked genome FASTA files
- map RNA (2-pass STAR), produce sorted/indexed BAMs and QC
- concatenate + cluster protein evidence (mmseqs easy-linclust)
- run BRAKER3 per assembly

Main dry-run:
snakemake do_all --slurm --default-resources slurm_account=thymusvulgaris \
  --configfile configs/config.yaml --use-conda -j 40 -c 20 -pn

Optional dry-runs by stage:
snakemake do_prepare_proteins --slurm --default-resources slurm_account=thymusvulgaris \
  --configfile configs/config.yaml --use-conda -j 20 -c 40 -pn

snakemake do_map_rna_all --slurm --default-resources slurm_account=thymusvulgaris \
  --configfile configs/config.yaml --use-conda -j 40 -c 80 -pn

Single-assembly annotation target example:
snakemake results/gene_annotation/ger5_hap1/braker/braker.gtf \
  --slurm --default-resources slurm_account=thymusvulgaris \
  --configfile configs/config.yaml --use-conda -j 20 -c 40 -pn

For real runs, remove -n.
